🔖 Save for your 🇻🇳 trip! Keep in mind that for them ‘fish sauce’ or ‘fish oil’ and eggs are vegetarian. So be specific when you are requesting for food. Tell them that you do not eat meat, or eggs and most people will whip you up something fresh & vegetarian! (Google translate will be your bestie!) 👏🏻🍀

And if you really can’t do without Indian cuisine, then every touristy place has multiple desi restaurants. It will be much more expensive than local cuisine though. 💸

Also, wanted to let you all know that I eat eggs, but I can’t consume eggs everyday, I don’t like them much and there are phases. I ended eating a lot of it on the trip though because I did not want to miss out on the food made by locals. Even if you do not consume eggs, you will get a lot of tofu, broccoli & greens to eat almost everywhere there! 🧀
